class Schedule extends Component  {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props) //since we are extending class Table so we have to use super in order to override Component class constructor
    // this.state = products
  }
  renderTableData() {
    return this.state.products.map((product, index) => {
       const { bus_type, source, destination, ddate, departure_time, arrival_time, fare, stops, available_seats,status, booking } = product //destructuring
       return (
          <tr key={Math.floor(Math.random() * 30)}>
             <td>{bus_type}</td>
             <td>{source}</td>
             <td>{destination}</td>
             <td>{ddate}</td>
             <td>{departure_time}</td>
             <td>{arrival_time }</td>
             <td>{fare}</td>
             <td>{stops}</td>
             <td>{available_seats }</td>
             <td>{status}</td>
             <td>{booking}</td>
          </tr>
       )
    })
 }
 renderTableHeader() {
  let header = Object.keys(this.state.productss[0])
  return header.map((key, index) => {
     return <th key={index}>{key.toUpperCase()}</th>
  })
}
  render() { //Whenever our class runs, render method will be called automatically, it may have already defined in the constructor behind the scene.
    return (
      <div>
         <h1 id='title'>React Dynamic Table</h1>
         <table id='student'>
            <tbody>
               <tr>{this.renderTableHeader()}</tr>
               {this.renderTableData()}
            </tbody>
         </table>
      </div>
   )
 }
}
export default Schedule;
